article.headline: James scores 23 on 8-of11 shooting
article.story:
MIAMI (Ticker) -- Tamara James scored 23 points and senior 
Chanivia Broussard recorded 19 points and eight rebounds as No.
21 Miami defeated Providence, 81-62, in the Big East Conference
regular season finale for both teams Tuesday.

The Hurricanes shot 51 percent (18-for-35) from the field in the
first half to take a 40-25 lead at halftime.

James went 8-of-11 from the floor and added five rebounds and
four steals in 30 minutes off the bench.

Broussard, who was honored before the game along with fellow
seniors Vera Arsova, Shaquana Wilkins and Hutashi Wilson, fell
four points shy of a career high set in 2002 against Syracuse.

Wilkins registered 13 points and 14 boards and Wilson chipped in
eight points and five assists for Miami (22-5, 11-5 Big East),
which has won six of its last seven games.

The Hurricanes tied for fourth in the league, but will receive a
first-round bye in the upcoming Big East Conference Tournament
because they hold the tiebreaker over Boston College.

Gayle Nwafili poured in 25 points to lead the Friars (4-23, 0-16
Big East), who have dropped nine of their last 11 games against
Miami.

Kristin Quinn contributed 12 points and six steals off the bench
for Providence, which has lost 16 games in a row.
